<div class="space-y-8">
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Basics</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      LongShot is an app where you create golf pools for PGA Tour events. Create a pool, add tournaments, invite your friends—then see who really knows their long shots.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
      <li>Each pool can include one or more PGA Tour tournaments.</li>
      <li>For each tournament, every member makes 4 picks. No copying—you lock in your own lineup.</li>
      <li>Scores for all tournaments in the pool are added up. Climb the standings and take the bragging rights.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">How to Win</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      You earn points from the prize money your picks win. Picking long-odds players pays off with a bonus—so the name fits. Beat the favorites; go for the sleepers.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      Your score per pick is <strong>prize money + odds bonus</strong>—but the bonus only counts if your pick
      <strong>makes the cut</strong>. The bonus is <strong>20× the odds</strong> (locked when the tournament starts).
      The long-shot bonus is capped at 10% of the tournament's total prize pool.
      Think of a long shot at +4500 who sneaks into the weekend: they earn a <strong>90,000-point bonus</strong> (4500 × 20)
      plus whatever prize money they take home. If your pick misses the cut, you get 0 points for that pick. Longer odds mean a bigger payoff when your pick performs—and more to brag about.
      Players whose odds would hit this cap are marked with an asterisk (*) where picks and results are shown.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">When Picks Open and Lock</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      Fair and simple: no one can see your lineup until it’s time.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
      <li><strong>Picks open</strong> exactly <strong>4 days before the tournament starts</strong>.</li>
      <li>Before then, you’ll see when they open—no “Make picks” link yet.</li>
      <li>From open until tee time, make or tweak your picks as much as you want.</li>
      <li>Once the tournament starts, picks are <strong>locked</strong>. No take-backs. May the best lineup win.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Who Can See Which Picks?</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      We keep it fair before play, then full transparency once it’s on:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
      <li><strong>Before the tournament starts</strong>:
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>You always see your own picks.</li>
          <li>For everyone else, you only see “Pick submitted” or “No pick”—not who they picked. No copying, no spoilers.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>After the tournament starts</strong>:
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>All picks are revealed. Compare lineups, own your wins, and (gently) roast the misses.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Managing Your Pool</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      You run the pool; we keep the competition clean.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
      <li>The pool creator adds tournaments and can remove members.</li>
      <li>Standings show every member and their total—the leaderboard everyone’s gunning for.</li>
      <li>From Standings: <strong>leave the pool</strong> yourself, or (if you’re the creator) <strong>remove</strong> someone. Keep it fun, keep it fair.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>

